title: China provides medical supplies to the Panama Ministry of Agricultural Development in April 2020
description: On April 3, 2020, China donated masks, gloves and other hygienic supplies to the Ministry of Agricultural Development in Panama. These supplies will be used to support collaborators who are working on the front lines of the pandemic to prepare and distribute food bags throughout the country. The monetary value of this donation is unknown.

title: Chinese government provides masks to Mayor's Office of Panama City in April 2020
description: On April 8, 2020, the Chinese government donated 10,000 masks to the Mayor’s Office of Panama City. These masks will be utilized by staff and working personnel of the office. They will be distributed among collaborators of the Municipality of Panama, the Houses of Peace, and the Municipal Police. The monetary value of this donation is unknown. Mayor José Luis Fábrega accepted this donation which was handed over by the Chinese Embassy.
staff_comments: AidData has estimated the transaction amount for this donation based on price catalogues from the World Health Organization (WHO). Please see the TUFF Methodology for additional details.

title: Chinese Embassy donates masks to the Los Santos Government in April 2020

title: Chinese automaker Jiangling Motors (JMC) donates ambulance to Panama in April 2020
description: On April 21, 2020, Chinese automaker Jiangling Motors (JMC) donated an ambulance to Panamanian Ministry of Health to support their fight against COVID-19.  Ambulances were also sent to the Ministries of Health of Bolivia, Egypt, Myanmar and Vietnam. A donation ceremony for the ambulances was held at the JMC Factory in Xiaolan. Qiu Tiangao, secretary of the party committee and chairman of Jiangling Group, and chairman of Jiangling Co., Ltd., announced the donation. Jin Wenhui, the first executive vice president of JMC presided over the donation ceremony.

title: Qingyuan Municipal Government grants 500 bags of food to the Colón District of Panama for anti-epidemic efforts in April 2020
description: On April 28, 2020, 500 bags of food were delivered to the Colón District Mayor's Office by the Qingyuan Municipal Government of the People's Republic of China.   These food bags will be distributed among families in need across different sectors, according to Alex Lee, the Mayor of the District of Colón, in the wake of the pandemic. The monetary value of this donation is unknown.
